inn1.comm: begins on a length, just outside off, Watson well forward to defend
leg-side half-volley, but flicked straight to square leg
another full ball into the pads, driven straight to mid-on
short of a length, outside off, dabbed away to third man for one
length ball, outside off, no movement. Left alone
short of a length, on off, angling away, defended off the back foot
full and straight, defended
full, on off, presses forward and nicely pushes this between the bowler and mid-off

McClenaghan strikes early again. Watson goes. Slight short of driving length, Watson pushes at it away from the body, and tentatively. The angle takes the edge, and Australia's own Luke Ronchi takes the catch
drives hard at a wide length ball, is hit on the inside half of the bat. It falls short of midwicket
full, swinging in, pushed towards mid-on
angling into the pads, beats him flicks, but goes fine off the pad
this one seams away from the left-hand batsman. Mills bowls really well to them. He bowls it with a scrambled seam, and it almost dips and cuts away from him. Beaten
short of a length, seams away again. Squares him up and beats him
left alone outside off this time
short of a length, pitches leg, angles towards off, defended off the back foot
short of a length, outside off, punched away to third man - no England player there - for one
short of a length, middle and leg, angling towards off, defended off the back foot

it's Guptill again. Hughes can't get rid of Guptill, who is not even in the slip. Hughes has not even played this ball, but Guptill has still got him. Wade looks to drop and run, but both batsmen hesitate. Guptill runs in from cover, swoops in, flicks this onto the stumps even as he dives. Guptill sends Hughes back again
length ball, on off, defended back by George Bailey
short of a length, middle and off, seams away, squares him up and beats him
short of a length, hits his pad for a leg-bye. He has overstepped
nice slower wide yorker to get a dot on the free-hit
short of a length, Wade moves too far across, hit on the pad just outside the line of off
runs this down to third man for one
short of a length, pitched outside leg, angling towards off, defended back to him
that's a punch, and is beneficial to Australia. Short of a length, outside off, he stands tall and crunches this through cover
short, but stays low, and takes the inside edge on the pull
fuller, outside off, angling away, left alone
nicely pulled away. This is short, waist high, on the pads, and Wade obliges by punishing it through square leg
short of a length, middle and leg, angling away, defended off the back foot
beauty. Shaping up to swing in, but pitching just outside off and seaming away. Beaten
on a length, in front of off, defended
short of a length, pitched outside leg, worked away to long leg for one
shuffles across to a full swinging ball, but gets the bat down in time and takes a single to long leg
length ball outside leg, clipped away, and they take on Franklin's arm from long leg. Wade puts in a full-length dive to complete the second
defended off the front foot

huge appeal for catch at the wicket. This one seems to have seamed away from middle and leg and taken a deflection on the way through to the keeper. Wade is squared up, he has played inside the line, and the ball has taken the back thigh on the way. Vettori tells everybody not to review this, and rightly so. Vettori should know the pain of wasted reviews
left alone outside off
seam again. The scrambled-seam ball cuts away from on off, and beats Wade
fuller and straighter. Defended from the crease
beaten outside off again. Tentative again as he pushes away from the body
short of a length, pitches middle and leg, angles towards off. Defended
slider first up, defended off the front foot
flatter, on off, Bailey pushes half forward in defence
short of a length, outside off, pushed wide of cover for one
pitched up, middle and leg, defended to short midwicket
Wade comes down the track to drive this to deep midwicket
defended off the front foot
dug in shirt, not short enough to pull, and Wade is hit in the box. B McCullum likes it and applauds
length ball, outside off, left alone
short of a length, angling away towards off, defended under his eye
beats a slash as Mills pitches up and Wade swings. Bounces short of Ronchi
short of a length, pitched outside leg, Wade goes inside the line and works it to leg for one
pitched up full, just outside off, driven back to Mills
some turn from middle and leg, hits his pad and goes to short fine leg
down the wicket to defend a full ball
arm ball, Wade moves across and picks it from the pitch, and somehow keeps it out
looks to paddle, gloves it to short fine leg for a risky single
swept away wide of long leg for a couple
short of a length, outside off, punched away for one
looks to work this to leg, gets a leading edge to wide of cover for one
bunted wide of fine leg and with soft hands, and he takes another frenetic couple
pulled away to deep midwicket for one
slightly slower, shaping in, defended off the front foot
short, not short enough to pull, and beats him
nice shot. Length ball, angling into the pads, driven between mid-on and midwicket
short of a length, outside leg, deflected to short fine
tossed up, on the pads, clipped away
flat but full, defended off the front foot
short of a length, outside off, looks to dab it fine, but finds point
defended well off the front foot
slightly short, he rocks back and punches this to the right of the diving backward point and to the left of deep cover
full, on middle and leg, pushed wide of mid-on for one
overpitched, and Bailey drives it beautifully. It has gone over the stumps at the non-striker's end, I think
overpitched again, no swing again, but driven right back to him this time
short of a length, wide, Bailey goes back and punches. Misfield at backward point gets them two
too full again, on the pads too, and he has driven it nicely through mid-on for four. No fielder at mid-on either. Over attacking?
clipped away off the pads for one
slow through the air, full, middle and leg, defended by Bailey
shimmies down the wicket to defend this flatter delivery
swept away fine of long leg, comes back for the second
down the wicket, beaten in the flight, pads this away
looks to paddle this away, but finds the man at short midwicket
swept in the air, but it falls short of the man in the deep
flighted on middle and leg, driven back to him
flat, on off, defended back to him
driven down the ground, but can't beat mid-on
full, outside off, driven to long-on
full toss on the pads, gets a single to deep midwicket
moves right across a length ball and works it to leg. That's a risky shot against Vettori
into the pads, beats the inside edge, hits the pad
slower through the air, shortish, outside off, but Bailey doesn't offer a shot
arm ball, angling in towards off, defended off the back foot
slower through the air again, and Bailey is drawn forward to defend
full, middle and leg, defended to mid-on
defended off the front foot
flighted outside off, slow, defended again
down the wicket, not quite to its pitch, but goes ahead with the shot and drags it wide of mid-on
defended off the front foot
shimmies down, is beaten, but defends well in front of his body
short of a length, into the pads, bunted away for one
tossed up outside off, defended wide of cover. Bailey wants a single, but is sent back
goes back, gets a single into the leg side
short of a length, but slower, defended off the back foot
sharp turn, angling in, dipping, then breaks away to beat the forward defensive
not quite the slider. He remains slow and flights it. Defended well
now comes the slider, he keeps the front leg away and defends with the bat only
down the leg side. Called wide
worked away off the pad
tossed up outside off, Bailey tries to sweep, but is beaten
flighted wide outside off, driven to straight midwicket
tries to reverse-sweep, is beaten by a full and wide delivery
nearly a run-out. Pushed towards short midwicket, Guptill charges in, nearly gets him on the single

Wade goes. N McCullum gets this to straighten enough. Flat length ball, angling into the pads, Wade plays across its line, the ball straightens and beats the edge, and he is caught dead in front. They review it, but he is gone plumb. That's what DRS is not for. What a waste
down the wicket to defend this to short midwicket
pushed wide of midwicket for one
short of a length, outside off, pushed to point
defended off the front foot
really slow and high, defends, is hit on the outside half of the bat, runs a tight single
short of a length, on off, worked to leg for one
swept away from outside off
nearly a return catch. Bowled from the front of the hand, stops in the pitch, but the drive dies before reaching McCullum
short of a length, outside off, punched to the right of third man
defended off the front foot
full and straight, driven back to his right
down the wicket to drive this down to long-on
angling into the pads, pushed between the two men deep on the leg side
short of a length, outside off, cut to cover
arm ball, defended off the back foot
more turn for Vettori. He tosses up one outside off, Voges pushes in front of his body, and is beaten
straighter, but a turning ball, and is defended well off the front foot
gets a leading edge on this as he looks to work this to leg
pushed down to long-on for one
driven to short straight midwicket
down the wicket, the ball dips on him, he ends up pushing it into the leg side
short of a length, on off, punched down to long-on
tossed up outside off, defended to leg
short of a length, outside off, cut away to deep point
pushed to deep cover
on a length, on off, pushed to mid-off for one
on a length, outside off, pushed to mid-off, but this time a little too hard to be taking the single
full, swinging in, clipped to leg. McCullum dives on that matting to over the adjacent pitch and scrapes his elbow
driven on the up to deep cover
short of a length, turning in, pushed into the leg side. A misfield from McClenaghan allows them the second
full, middle and off, driven to long-on
short of a length, turning in towards off, pushed to long-on for one
short of a length, outside off, cut away to deep cover
allows himself to be but away again for a single
short of a length, turning in, worked to leg for one
swinging in from a length, hits the inside half of the bat. Was that reverse swing?

appeal for leg-before as Voges moves a long way across and it seems to have hit him in front. Given not out. Nigel Llong thinks this is headed down leg. New Zealand don't review. That looks very close
another appeal as the swing beats the inside edge, but this is clearly missing leg
Nathan McCullum has saved four here. Makes a full-length diving save to his left at mid-on, and nearly hits the stumps at the striker's end
length ball, driven on the up, to mid-off
short of a length, on off, defended off the front foot
lovely start right away. Seams away from him on off, beats the edge
length ball outside leg, pushed wide of mid-on for one
full outside off, pushed to mid-on
on a length, angling towards off, pushed wide of mid-on for one
lovely off-drive. On the up because this is no driving length, and placed between the bowler and mid-off
another drive, but this is straight to the fielder at mid-off
swing in again, hits the inside half of the bat on the drive
beautiful. Lovely drive. This is swinging in but not alarmingly, and he presses forward and pushes this to the right of the stumps at the non-striker's end
another beautiful drive. Southee has got carried away looking for swing here. Another half-volley, and he has drilled this between mid-off and cover
on-drive now, but the mid-on has been moved back
swinging in from short of a driving length. Defended to leg
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot
short of a length, turning in from outside off, punched away for a single
tossed up outside off, driven straight to short cover
down the wicket, mis-hits a loft, it goes to long-on on the second bounce
cut away to deep cover
punched away uppishly, BMac makes a diving save at short cover
swept away from outside off, between the two men deep on the leg side. That brings up a fighting fifty for Bailey. Well done, captain
short of a length, pitched outside leg, Voges gets inside the line and deflects it nicely for four through fine leg
that's poor from Mitch. Are you sure this is the correct Mitch? No-ball, outside leg, and deflected away for four more
goes for the wide yorker on the free hit, and is called a wide
slower short ball on  the free hit, pulled away for just the single. Didn't really hit it like you hit a free hit
short of a length, on the pads, worked away for one
gets this shortish ball to hold its line. Dropped wide of cover for one. McCullum overthrows for the second. New Zealand seem to be getting carried away
slower ball outside off, gets a dot ball in
short of a length, angling in, worked into the leg side
short of a length, angling in, worked to leg for one
short of a length, outside off, punched to straight midwicket
down the wicket to work this full ball into the leg side
short of a length, into the pads, quick, Voges gets enough bat on it to beat short fine leg. This is running away from NZ
flighted outside off, defended back to him
driven back to his right, KW makes a diving save
full, on off, driven to extra cover
looks to dab a fullish ball, can't beat the two men behind square
defended off the front foot
angling in, flat, defended to leg
flat outside off, holds its line, beats his push
slower through the air, gets some turn, hits the outside half of the bat. A maiden for NZ
defended off the front foot
down the wicket, is beaten in flight, but gets a leg-bye
looks to play across the line, is beaten, but has got the front pad outside the line of off
defended into the leg side for one
Guptill misfield at midwicket. Allows them a single
defended solidly off the front foot
full, outside off, driven to extra cover
full, into the pads, worked around the corner for one
dips on him, but is too straight, and is helped into the leg side for one
defended off the front foot as Vettori goes flatter
slower through the air, on off, holds its line, defended solidly
this one comes in with the arm, and hits the inside half of his bat
short of a length, cut away to deep cover for one
short of a length, looks to work this to leg but the ball doesn't turn. Defended back
full, driven to long-on for one
full and flat, pushed to long-on to bring up an industrious fifty
down the wicket, nearly yorks himself up. Played back to him

McNath has taken a wicket off the last ball before the Powerplay. Flat length ball outside off, Bailey believes he has covered any turn possible, but the ball seems to have hit some rough pacth and stayed low and spun past the pad to hit the lower half of the middle stump
length ball outside off, defended off the front foot
just short of long-on. Not the smartest of shots. The long-on is in place, but he has gone there aerially. It falls short
short of a length, outside off, defended
defended past the silly point to cover
defended back to him
tossed up outside off, defended to cover
tossed up on off, defended to leg
stays back to push this to the right of midwicket where Guptill is quick and flashy but his throw is wide and allows them the second
full outside off, driven to long-on
short of a length, outside off, punched to mid-off
tries the big drive outside off, gets an inside edge onto the pad
defended off the front foot
short of a length, outside off, gets it to bounce, played back to him
tossed up outside off, worked to leg for one
full, middle and leg, takes the leading edge on his drive. Goes to point
short and straight, worked to leg
turning in from outside off, worked to deep square with soft hands, gets a couple
flighted outside off, driven to long-off
offbreak, hits the inside half of the bat, but they take the single
full outside off, driven to long-on for one
short, a long hop, into the pads, and pulled away for four through square leg
flighted outside off, defended to cover this time
slower through the air, defended with soft hands, gets a single to short third man
on a length, outside off, defended off the front foot
short of a length, wide, he throws his bat at it, gets a thick outside edge for four. Past the keeper and straight of short third man
short of a length again, turning in towards off, defended off the back foot
beautiful shot. Tossed up outside off, he presses forward to reach the pitch of the ball and drives it wide of cover
fuller, and flatter, defended back to him
turns into the pads, worked around the corner for one
sharp turn from short of a length outside off, he nearly plays it on off the bottom edge
full, outside off, defended to leg
short of a length, into the pads, worked to leg
looks for a big cover drive, inside-edges onto the pads
turns in towards off, defended off the front foot
reverse-sweep this time. Takes this from off, and places it wide of short third man
tossed up outside off, driven to cover. McNath today: 46 for 2 in his 10
length ball outside off, driven to deep cover for one
another lovely drive from Voges. On the up, between the bowler and mid-off. Past the dive of the long-on coming across
slower ball, pushed to mid-off for one
slower bouncer, just outside leg. Called a wide
short of a length, tucked away off the hip, soft hands, they get two before deep midwicket comes in
slower ball again, on a length, cutting away, nicely played with an open face, fine of third man
not short enough for the pull. He is on the front foot when he decides to pull this shortish delivery. He is totally cramped, and top-edges it to the keeper
full outside off, pushed to short midwicket
tries the reverse-sweep but finds short third man this time
flatter, into the pads, he works this around the corner
looks to work this to leg, gets a leading edge back to him
short of a length, turning in, pushed with an open face for a single
turning in, gets across the line and inside the ball, takes a single to short fine leg

Mitchell has got a Mitchell Johnson wicket. A full toss to short cover. The full toss is outside off and angling away, Voges wants to shovel it to leg, but ends up slicing it straight to short cover. Big wicket of the set batsman
length ball, outside off, defended off the front foot
short of a length, tucked away off the hip for one
short of a length down the leg side, called a wide
cut away to deep point
short of a length, outside off, pushed to the left of cover for one
short, outside off, pulled wide of deep midwicket for a couple
short of a length, turning in, dropped wide of cover for one
turning in from outside off, past the inside edge, but the umpire rules this is headed down leg
driven into the off side
driven back to him this time
moves inside the line for a shortish ball, gets a single to short fine leg
this one dips on him and beats him in the flight. Concedes just the leg-bye
slower ball, he charges at it, drives it to long-on, where McNath is lighting quick to get to his left and let a ripper back to Mitch. They can't think of the second
short of a length, the angle beats the big drive
slower short ball, he is early to charge down the wicket, and ends up hitting this straight to short cover
full and wide, beats his drive, but goes for a bye after the ball bounces in front of Ronchi and slips away
slower legcutter? It definitely came back in. Definitely it is a chinaman. Beats Maxweel's slog and hits him on the pad
the bouncer this time, and Maxwell is on a premeditated charge down the wicket. Bottom-edges it to the keeper
short of a length, on off, punched wide of deep cover
pushed through, worked to leg, but can't beat short midwicket
slows it down this time, Faulkner wants to clear mid-off, but ends up hitting off the lower half of the bat, and drills it straight and waist high to McClenaghan
this one turns from a length outside off, takes the thick outside edge. They are hesitant with the one, and Johnson is sent back
driven straight to cover this time
short of a length, outside off, punched to cover
full outside off, driven to deep cover
nonchalantly done. A length ball, angling in towards off, he moves across and paddles this fine between the keeper and short fine leg
full toss, angling in towards leg, and Johnson makes room to drive this between mid-off and cover. All along the ground. This Mitch, too, is all right

slower short ball, and as a correspondent suggested, it's McClenaghanain. And again and again. Slower short ball, digs into the pitch, comes off very slow, and he has hit it straight to cover. That, if I am not wrong, is the most wickets for anybody after nine matches
length ball outside off, pushed to cover
short of a length, on off, defended
short of a length, down the leg side, worked away to short fine leg for one
full, into the pads, comes down the wicket to drag this over wide long-on for six. Didn't Australia need it some?
this time he lets the ball go, and bowls full outside off, and Maxwell reverses this over point for four
too short. An over too many from spin? Maxwell rocks back and pulls this way over deep square leg for a six
full and fast, gets the toe edge for one
slower through the air, Maxwell turns down the single and keeps the strike for the last over
good slower bouncer, Maxwell is so far off the rhythm he doesn't even play at it. Called one for the over
full and straight, hit wide of mid-off, but refuses the single again
slower ball gone wrong. Too high a full toss. A no-ball for sure. Chest high. Misses
short of a length, angling away, actually cuts away a little, beats Maxwell's slog
short cutter again, pulled away, wide of long-on, takes the second
slower bouncer again, beats Maxwell's attempt to upper-cut. That's the second bouncer of the over
slogged away to long-on, comes back for two... he has absolutely risked the second, but he has made it

inn2.comm: Ronchi has smoked it first ball. Wide length ball, and he drives on the up and through covers for four
extra bounce. Short of a length, outside off, kicks away chest-high. Ronchi fends at it, and is beaten
length ball outside off, he wants to pull out of the shot, but is late and ends up guiding it wide of point for one
short, gets good bounce, down the leg side, at 147ks. Not called wide presumably because Guptill has moved too far inside the line
fuller, slight swing back in towards off, watchfully played back to him
fuller, on off, covers the swing, pushes to mid-on
short of a length, cuts back in, cramps his cut
wide length ball, left alone
this one seams back in from short of a length, and hits him on the thigh pad
length ball outside off, left alone this time
slower ball, wide length ball, hit off the outside half of bat, in the air, wide of point
short of a length, angling in, defended to mid-on
short of a length, pitched outside leg, he rises with it, places it wide of mid-on, takes three
full, outside off, nicely driven, but straight to mid-off
short of a length again, and timed well wide of mid-on for two more
lovely driving by Guptill. Give him the best car in the world, I don't see a better driver around. He stands tall, drives this length ball on the up, through cover, all along the ground
wide full toss, and Johnson nearly gets a typical Johnson wicket. Goes off the toe end, but doesn't carry to cover
full, outside off, driven straight to short cover
wide length ball, not as quick as he expects, edges it to third man for one
short of a length, seaming in, worked into the leg side for one
wide length ball, stops a touch, Guptill checks the drive, and defends to point
full, on off, driven nicely again, but straight to mid-on
wide length ball, Guptill drives again, but is not close to it, and is beaten
the slow pitch does in for Guptill who has been driving at most of the deliveries. McKay has been getting the ball to stop a little, and so it does again. Guptill gets a thick edge to backward point
short of a length, angling in, defended to midwicket
short of a length, angling in, defended to mid-on
short of a length again, accurate too, defended off the back foot
angling into the pads, Ronchi misses out on the gift. Gets just the leg-bye

half-volley, on off, driven sweetly and straight to mid-off, but they still go for the run. Williamson is not the quickest, doesn't have the biggest strides, doesn't put the dive in, but Johnson's throw misses from mid-off
early into the drive again, but this one flies between point and cover
short of a length, wide, left alone
short of a length, down the leg side, called a wide
uppish drive again, the ball stops again, but this doesn't carry to mid-on
short of a length, nips back in from wide outside off, left alone. Not too far from the off stump
short of a length, outside off, defended to point
nips back in from short of a length, defended
short of a length, tucked away off the hip for a single
defended off the front foot
on a length, angling in, driven to mid-on
short, wide, seams away to beat the cut
leg-side half-volley, pushed straight to mid-on
short of a length, just outside off, defended off the back foot
short of a length, outside off, pushed to cover
soft soft dismissal. There is a man placed at fourth slip-gully slot, and Ronchi has run a shortish ball straight down his throat
first ball Taylor drives a half-volley to the left of cover and gets a couple
dabbed to third man for one
short of a length, bouncing, he rides the bounce and fends with soft hands, towards the slip
short and wide, cut away hard into the pitch, and gets it to bounce over the head of the fielder at point. . Called one short, but I think he had got just - only just - over the line
wide length ball, left alone
short of a length, thigh-high, punched away through square leg
full and on off, driven to mid-off
short of a length, on off, defended back to him
cut away, but finds point
wide length ball, defended with soft hands off the front foot
wide length ball, Williamson drives it on the up, all along the ground, between short cover and cover
short of a length, middle and leg, defended back to him
full, seaming away towards off, Taylor defends in front of his body
short of a length, outside off, seams a little, beats the outside edge
stays short of a length, angling away, defended off the back foot
length ball, on the pads, pushed towards mid-on for one
short of a length, pitches off, angles away, defended off the back foot
Bailey dives at short cover to field a sizzling drive from Taylor
short of a length, sliding, on off, defended well
stays short of a length, middle and leg, defended again
slower short ball, tucked off the hip for one
sharp short ball, over leg stump, he stays inside the line of it
good bouncer, 141ks, rising and rising, Williamson has to pull out of the hook
length ball, outside off, pushed through cover for one
short of a length, on off, punched to deep square leg for one
length ball, on off, defended to mid-off
short of a length, just outside off, defended to mid-off
length ball angling across him, takes the outside edge to third man
on a length, just outside off, defended off the front foot
short of a length, outside off, defended off the front foot
full, outside off, driven, but straight to short cover
short of a length, slower ball, beats the outside edge with the cut
driven wide of point off the outside half of the bat
short of a length, on off, defended outside off
short of a length, angling in, defended off the back foot
length ball, outside off, defended
driven on the up, to mid-on
short of a length, on off, he gets across the line and pushes it wide of mid-on for a couple
bouncer, on off, he ducks under it
bouncer, quite high, Williamson pulls, but it doesn't carry to deep midwicket
short of a length, seams back a touch, defended well
sharp turn first ball. Oh ho ho. Flat, angled in, and then it turns away across the face of the bat
flat, a little short, defended off the back foot
poor delivery, full, fast, down leg, paddled away fine of short fine leg
turn again, from middle and off towards off, defended off the front foot
full, into the pads, flicked away for one
tossed up outside off, defended back to him
